race.comment: SAFARI BOY (2) is still a maiden after 14 starts but looks well placed in this race on the back of a disappointing effort at Belmont last time out. Back to a race of this calibre looks ideal and if he gets some luck from the barrier, he'll be very hard to hold out. CANTILEVER (1) should be peaking now after finishing second over 1410m at this track last time at the third run of the campaign. Well placed and should go well again. FREAKISH BY NATURE (10) finished out of the money on debut two starts back then he settled well back and was beaten 6 lengths over 1400m contest at Northam nine days ago. Will enjoy a drop in class so he is set to turn things around. FLY AWAY FLIRT (11) was prominent until they straightened last time but weakened to finish seventh, beaten 4.5 lengths, over 1500m at York. This looks a nice race so expect her to finish closer. BEST RESULT (7) is next best.
